  "prompt": "Who was the best teacher or professor you ever had? What made him or her the best?",
  "response": "One of the best teachers I've learned about was someone who created an inspiring and supportive learning environment. This teacher was known for their passion for the subject matter and their ability to make complex topics accessible and engaging. They treated every student with respect and encouraged open dialogue, ensuring everyone felt valued and heard. By providing personalized feedback and support, they fostered students' individual growth and instilled a lifelong love of learning. Additionally, their innovative teaching methods and real-world applications made the lessons memorable and impactful. This combination of enthusiasm, empathy, and expertise is often what makes a teacher truly exceptional.",
